  "prompt": "Why does Peter Thiel hate Gawker?",
  "response": "Peter Thiel's animosity toward Gawker Media stems from a personal incident involving the publication of an article about him in 2007, which outed him as gay. Thiel felt that the article was an invasion of his privacy and contributed to a broader culture of harassment and bullying. \n\nIn response to his feelings about Gawker, Thiel later became a financial backer of the lawsuit against the company launched by Hulk Hogan (Terry Bollea), which ultimately led to Gawker's bankruptcy. Thiel's involvement in that case was seen as a way to hold Gawker accountable for what he considered unethical and aggressive practices in journalism. His actions have sparked debate about press freedom, privacy, and the power dynamics in media.",
